stimulusHtml: At point C, is  d y d t MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3D33@  positive? At point C, is  d x d t MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3D32@  positive? Give a reason for each answer.

features.html: A particle starts at point A on the positive x-axis at time t = 0 and travels along the curve from A to B to C to D, as shown above. The coordinates of the particle's position (x(t), y(t)) are differentiable functions of t, where  x ′ ( t ) = d x d t = − 9 cos ( π t 6 ) sin ( π t + 1 2 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@@56F8@ and  y ′ ( t ) = d y d t MathType@MTEF@5@5@@41E4@  is not explicitly given. At time t = 9, the particle reaches its final position at point D on the positive x-axis.
